BEGIN_PGML_HINT

Proof that [`` \lim_{x\rightarrow 1} 2x+1=3``]:

Let [`\varepsilon = \frac{\delta}{2}`]

Assume [`0<|x-1|<\delta`]

[`
\begin{aligned}
|f(x)-L|=|2x+1-3|&=|2x-2|\\
&=|2|\cdot |x-1|\\
&< 2 \delta\\
&=2\cdot \varepsilon/2\\
&=\varepsilon\\
\end{aligned}
`]




